{"questionId":"27746576","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Let&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y = {\\left( {{x^3} + x} \\right)^{\\frac{3}{2}}}\">\n  <mi>y</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>(</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <msup>\n              <mi>x</mi>\n              <mn>3</mn>\n            </msup>\n          </mrow>\n          <mo>+</mo>\n          <mi>x</mi>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>)</mo>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mfrac>\n          <mn>3</mn>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </mfrac>\n      </mrow>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Consider the functions&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f\\left( x \\right) = \\sqrt {{x^3} + x} \">\n  <mi>f</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <msqrt>\n    <mrow>\n      <msup>\n        <mi>x</mi>\n        <mn>3</mn>\n      </msup>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>+</mo>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n  </msqrt>\n</math></span> and <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"g\\left( x \\right) = 6 - 3{x^2}\\sqrt {{x^3} + x} \">\n  <mi>g</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>6</mn>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>3</mn>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <msqrt>\n    <mrow>\n      <msup>\n        <mi>x</mi>\n        <mn>3</mn>\n      </msup>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>+</mo>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n  </msqrt>\n</math></span>, for <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span> ≥ 0.</p>\n<p>The graphs of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f\">\n  <mi>f</mi>\n</math></span> and <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"g\">\n  <mi>g</mi>\n</math></span> are shown in the following diagram.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/5b0f80125baff3ae7116b512e054609e5627f40d.png\"></p>\n<p>The shaded region <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"R\">\n  <mi>R</mi>\n</math></span> is enclosed by the graphs of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f\">\n  <mi>f</mi>\n</math></span>, <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"g\">\n  <mi>g</mi>\n</math></span>, the <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y\">\n  <mi>y</mi>\n</math></span>-axis and <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x = 1\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>1</mn>\n</math></span>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Hence find the exact area of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"R\">\n  <mi>R</mi>\n</math></span>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>recognizing <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\sqrt {{x^3} + x} \">\n  <msqrt>\n    <mrow>\n      <msup>\n        <mi>x</mi>\n        <mn>3</mn>\n      </msup>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>+</mo>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n  </msqrt>\n</math></span> is a common factor (seen anywhere, may be seen in part (c))&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em>eg</em>&nbsp; &nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\left( { - 3{x^2} - 1} \\right)\\sqrt {{x^3} + x} \">\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mn>3</mn>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>x</mi>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mn>1</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <msqrt>\n    <mrow>\n      <msup>\n        <mi>x</mi>\n        <mn>3</mn>\n      </msup>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>+</mo>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n  </msqrt>\n</math></span>,&nbsp; <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\int {6 - \\left( {3{x^2} + 1} \\right)} \\sqrt {{x^3} + x} \">\n  <mo>∫</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mn>6</mn>\n    <mo>−</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mo>(</mo>\n      <mrow>\n        <mn>3</mn>\n        <mrow>\n          <msup>\n            <mi>x</mi>\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </msup>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>+</mo>\n        <mn>1</mn>\n      </mrow>\n      <mo>)</mo>\n    </mrow>\n  </mrow>\n  <msqrt>\n    <mrow>\n      <msup>\n        <mi>x</mi>\n        <mn>3</mn>\n      </msup>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>+</mo>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n  </msqrt>\n</math></span>,&nbsp; &nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\left( {3{x^2} - 1} \\right)\\sqrt {{x^3} + x} \">\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>3</mn>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>x</mi>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mn>1</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <msqrt>\n    <mrow>\n      <msup>\n        <mi>x</mi>\n        <mn>3</mn>\n      </msup>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>+</mo>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n  </msqrt>\n</math></span></p>\n<p>correct integration&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(A1)(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>eg&nbsp; &nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"6x - \\frac{2}{3}{\\left( {{x^3} + x} \\right)^{\\frac{3}{2}}}\">\n  <mn>6</mn>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n    <mn>3</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>(</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <msup>\n              <mi>x</mi>\n              <mn>3</mn>\n            </msup>\n          </mrow>\n          <mo>+</mo>\n          <mi>x</mi>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>)</mo>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mfrac>\n          <mn>3</mn>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </mfrac>\n      </mrow>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>A1</strong> </em>for <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"6x\">\n  <mn>6</mn>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span> and award <em><strong>A1</strong> </em>for&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" - \\frac{2}{3}{\\left( {{x^3} + x} \\right)^{\\frac{3}{2}}}\">\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n    <mn>3</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>(</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <msup>\n              <mi>x</mi>\n              <mn>3</mn>\n            </msup>\n          </mrow>\n          <mo>+</mo>\n          <mi>x</mi>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>)</mo>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mfrac>\n          <mn>3</mn>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </mfrac>\n      </mrow>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>.</p>\n<p>substituting limits into <strong>their</strong> integrated function and subtracting (in any order)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em>eg</em>&nbsp; &nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"6 - \\frac{2}{3}{\\left( {{1^3} + 1} \\right)^{\\frac{3}{2}}}\">\n  <mn>6</mn>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n    <mn>3</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>(</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <msup>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n              <mn>3</mn>\n            </msup>\n          </mrow>\n          <mo>+</mo>\n          <mn>1</mn>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>)</mo>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mfrac>\n          <mn>3</mn>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </mfrac>\n      </mrow>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>,&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"0 - \\left[ {6 - \\frac{2}{3}{{\\left( {{1^3} + 1} \\right)}^{\\frac{3}{2}}}} \\right]\">\n  <mn>0</mn>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>[</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>6</mn>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mfrac>\n        <mn>2</mn>\n        <mn>3</mn>\n      </mfrac>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mrow>\n            <mrow>\n              <mo>(</mo>\n              <mrow>\n                <mrow>\n                  <msup>\n                    <mn>1</mn>\n                    <mn>3</mn>\n                  </msup>\n                </mrow>\n                <mo>+</mo>\n                <mn>1</mn>\n              </mrow>\n              <mo>)</mo>\n            </mrow>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <mfrac>\n              <mn>3</mn>\n              <mn>2</mn>\n            </mfrac>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>]</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span></p>\n<p>correct working&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>&nbsp;(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em>eg</em>&nbsp; &nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"6 - \\frac{2}{3} \\times 2\\sqrt 2 \">\n  <mn>6</mn>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n    <mn>3</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>×</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n  <msqrt>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n  </msqrt>\n</math></span>,&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"6 - \\frac{2}{3} \\times \\sqrt 4&nbsp; \\times \\sqrt 2 \">\n  <mn>6</mn>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n    <mn>3</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>×</mo>\n  <msqrt>\n    <mn>4</mn>\n  </msqrt>\n  <mo>×</mo>\n  <msqrt>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n  </msqrt>\n</math></span></p>\n<p>area of&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"R = 6 - \\frac{{4\\sqrt 2 }}{3}\\,\\,\\,\\left( { = 6 - \\frac{2}{3}\\sqrt 8 {\\text{,}}\\,\\,\\,6 - \\frac{2}{3} \\times {2^{\\frac{3}{2}}}{\\text{,}}\\,\\,\\,\\frac{{18 - 4\\sqrt 2 }}{3}} \\right)\">\n  <mi>R</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>6</mn>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>4</mn>\n      <msqrt>\n        <mn>2</mn>\n      </msqrt>\n    </mrow>\n    <mn>3</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mo>=</mo>\n      <mn>6</mn>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mfrac>\n        <mn>2</mn>\n        <mn>3</mn>\n      </mfrac>\n      <msqrt>\n        <mn>8</mn>\n      </msqrt>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>,</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n      <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n      <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n      <mn>6</mn>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mfrac>\n        <mn>2</mn>\n        <mn>3</mn>\n      </mfrac>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n          <mrow>\n            <mfrac>\n              <mn>3</mn>\n              <mn>2</mn>\n            </mfrac>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>,</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n      <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n      <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n      <mfrac>\n        <mrow>\n          <mn>18</mn>\n          <mo>−</mo>\n          <mn>4</mn>\n          <msqrt>\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </msqrt>\n        </mrow>\n        <mn>3</mn>\n      </mfrac>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1&nbsp; N3</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[6 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"27746576","referenceCode":"19M.1.SL.TZ2.S_10d","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Hence find the exact area of R .","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"d","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 6]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5 —Calculus","Topic 5 —Calculus","SL 5.3—Differentiating polynomials, n E Z","Topic 5 —Calculus","SL 5.5—Integration introduction, areas between curve and x axis","Topic 5 —Calculus","SL 5.10—Indefinite integration, reverse chain, by substitution","Topic 5 —Calculus","SL 5.11—Definite integrals, areas under curve onto x-axis and areas between curves"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}